.TH GIT-PR-READY 1 "2026-06-13" "git-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-pr-ready \- check whether a GitHub pull request is landable
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git pr-ready
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ number|url|branch ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git pr-ready
checks whether a GitHub pull request is open, non-draft, conflict-free, and has
passing checks. Without a target, it uses the pull request for the current
branch.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-porcelain
Print stable
.B key=value
output for scripts.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Pull request is ready.
.TP
.B 1
Pull request is not ready, or GitHub status could not be read.
.TP
.B 2
Usage or local environment error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-pr-stack (1),
.BR git-pr-land (1)
